4:
A report has arrived regarding the
quest put out by the Diviners'
Commission. The one to slay the
yokai brothers—it has ended in
failure.
5:
Such reports are alarmingly
common as of late... How idle and
useless they have become.
7:
It is clear to me that we should not
speak of ENDING the Hunt, but of
implementing more rigid
commandments!
8:
Allow us to oversee the Hunt—we
know it best. Only a life led in
loathing of yokai and in dedication
to training can yield success.
10:
I see. Is there anyone else who
wishes to speak their mind?
16:
Rengetsu, you fool! You speak out of
line!
18:
I am aware of my own insolence,
but I would implore you to heed my
words regardless.
27:
Ahh, that was terrifying! I was so
nervous.
31:
So you told them that removing the
commandments would actually
improve your work? Hehe, how
fascinating!
36:
It was terribly embarrassing... They
demanded that I provide proof of
my claims!
41:
So you got tasked with taking out
the two problematic yokai?
46:
Yes. I wish to show them that yokai
and humans can work together to
take down a common foe!
51:
And that is PRECISELY what we shall
do—because we share a dream!
55:
Rengetsu, were you able to say
everything you wanted to say?
64: Only total victory will convince them!
68:
Well then... Let's do this! Just like we
planned.
73:
You swindled travelers out of their
hard-earned funds!
75:
You robbed villages of their precious
rations AND injured many.
76:
You committed arson, while
intoxicated, merely to stave off
boredom.
79:
If you do not repent for your crimes
and turn yourselves in willingly, then
prepare to fight!
82:
Heheheh. You think your petty
human rules have any meaning to
us? Fool.
83:
Shall we make of her a new
plaything? Or simply rob her blind?
93:
Princess Inaba—NO, wait, that is not
right. I mean... Princess INAHO, at
your service!
105:
Are you not forgetting to say
something VERY important?
112:
Witness the power of humans and
yokai, in unison!
123:
Wow! That was so incredibly cool,
Inaho!
128:
Did you SEE that joint attack? We
moved as one!
137:
Yep. I'm not going to let you get in
Rengetsu and Inaho's way.
140:
Quiet! This doesn't concern you. We
must stop that foolish, arrogant girl
before she gains even more renown!
143: Your timing is really quite something.
149: Oh, that was excellent! So thrilling!
152:
Then I looked those elders in the
eyes and told them!
155:
When humans and yokai work
together, the end result is
undeniable!
158:
That triumphant look on your face is
well-deserved, Rengetsu!
163: What happened to the Spirit Hunt?
168:
Lord Suizen spoke out in favor of me
and the elders were forced to
acknowledge it—the
commandments have been ended.
171:
From now on, members will not be
bound to rigid rules, and will hunt
evil yokai however they wish—even
with the help of other yokai!
173:
And when we aren't working, we are
free to do what we please.
179:
You realized your dream—you can
help others AND enjoy life's finer
pleasures!
182:
Hehe. I guess all of my wishes did
come true, didn't they?
186:
You popped up out of nowhere back
there, without so much as a
warning. What ever will I do with you?
192:
L-Lord Suizen! My sincerest
apologies for my rudeness the other
day...
195:
Think nothing of it—it led to positive
change, after all.
199:
It certainly didn't hurt that you
pulled some strings to make it all
happen.
204:
Lord Suizen! I swear that I will
continue to give it my all!
209:
However, I would advise you to stay
away from that fool of a fox. She is
likely to impede your work.
218:
It's okay. I can have fun AND do my
work at the same time. I've learned
to accept both parts of myself.
221:
And I've realized that I need to have
it all! I suppose I'm greedy like that.
223:
From now on, I'm going to do
everything I want to, whenever I
want to—and I'll always do my best!
